data.enText: in a way that is not known or certain

data.chText: 不管怎么着，我们都不能让他见她。
data.enText: We must stop him from seeing her somehow.

data.chText: 我必须想方设法找份新工作。
data.enText: Somehow or other I must get a new job.

data.chText: 由于某种未知的原因；不知为什么；不知怎么地
data.enText: for a reason that you do not know or understand

data.chText: 不知为什么，我觉得不能信任他。
data.enText: Somehow, I don't feel I can trust him.

data.chText: 不知怎么地，她看上去变了。

tr: in some unspecified way or manner
example: he expected somehow to discover a woman who would love him
he tried to make is someway acceptable
he had me dead to rights but somehow I got away with it

value.def: You use somehow to say that you do not know or cannot say how something was done or will be done.

example.ex: We'll  manage somehow, you and me. I know we will...
example.tran: 我和你，我们总能应付过去的。我知道我们会的。

example.ex: Channel 4 arrived and somehow created a different role for television...
example.tran: 第四频道开播了，它在某种程度上为电视创造了一个不同的角色。

example.ex: Somehow Karin managed to cope with the demands of her career...
example.tran: 卡琳设法达到了其职业的要求。

example.ex: Somehow I knew he would tell me the truth...
example.tran: 不知何故，我总觉得他会把真相告诉我的。

example.ex: He's been very quiet and withdrawn, sort of different, somehow...
example.tran: 不知什么缘故，他最近十分沉默，有点异样。
这座城市好像有些不一样了。

value.tran: 不知怎样;用某种方法;不知什么缘故;不知怎的

trans: （表示无法或不想确切说明）某一，某些
你就能做到；当你相信的时候；你能取得；不知为什么你将；你就会做到
